org.rocketproplab.marginalstability.flightcomputer.comm

Class PacketRouter

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.rocketproplab.marginalstability.flightcomputer.comm.PacketRouter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PacketRelay

    public class PacketRouter
extends java.lang.Object
implements PacketRelay
    Routes packets of any type to their destination.
    The routing works by having a Map between the type and source of the packet to a list of listeners. Each time sendPacket or receivePacket is called the router looks up the listenerArray and iterates through with the given packet.
    sendPacket(Object, PacketSources) and recivePacket(Object, PacketSources) specify the PacketDirection for the packet but both broadcast to all the listeners for that packet type (the class of the object) and source. See dispatchPacket(Object, PacketSources, PacketDirection) for more information.
    Author:
    Max Apodaca

      • dispatchPacket

        private void dispatchPacket(java.lang.Object o,
                            PacketSources source,
                            PacketDirection direction)
        Dispatch a packet with the given direction to all of the appropriate listeners. The packet listeners are looked up based off of a combination between the direction and class hash.
        Parameters:
        o - The packet to be transmitted
        source - the sender of the packet
        direction - what direction the packet is being sent in
